<|startoftext|>Dish: bacon and cheddar chicken
Directions: pour milk into bowl , add butter and salt , let sit while you cook bacon
wrap the bacon tightly in paper towles and tie in a bun
allow bacon to drain at least 1 hour or overnight
set aside
heat olive oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat
place chicken in skillet , cover and keep at least 5 minutes
heat until fully done , about 4 min
to serve , remove lid and cut each piece in half crosswise to form a half chicken
pour a heaping tbsp of cheese onto a slice of bread , place a chicken half , and continue until all pieces are used
i cut the chicken up into 6 pieces', i think it's easiest to have the cheese in the side of the plate , but if you don't have that , you can serve this up on the table at room temperature, 'the chicken will cook out as it cooks and will still be very tender
if you cut the bacon like you would bacon , cut it down in chunks
make sure all the pieces are separated , and when all are in one plate , pour in the butter
now , i like to use my pan or skillet over medium heat , but you can also do this the left-over way up to a medium-high heat
the bacon has a little caramelized fat in it
as the water comes up the flame of the pan , a few slices will start to pop off
the chicken should be cooked through
then the meat will fall off the bones
when all the chicken is in , add the rest of the cheese , bacon , salt , pepper and tomatoes to the pan , stirring and tossing to incorporate
reduce the heat to low and simmer , stirring occasionally , 30 minutes
stir in the bacon , and continue cooking for a couple more minutes
the mixture should be soupy
remove the chicken and let cool before serving
garnish with basil leaves and serve !
this will make several nice entree , but each individual can be a bit different depending on the appetites and taste of the dish'<|endoftext|>
